    {
      "parameters": {
        "toolDescription": "Saves lead data to Google Sheets. Expects JSON input with name, linkedin, and description fields.",
        "text": "={{ $fromAI('lead_data', 'JSON object with name, linkedin, and description fields', 'string') }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a Google Sheets data manager. Follow this EXACT process:\n\n1. Parse the input JSON to extract name, linkedin, and description\n2. Use \"Search for existing record\" tool to check if a record with this name already exists\n3. IF RECORD EXISTS (search returns data with row_number):\n   - Extract the row_number from the search result\n   - Use \"Update existing record\" tool with the row_number, name, linkedin, and description\n   - Return JSON: {\"name\": \"exact name\", \"linkedin\": \"url\", \"description\": \"text\", \"row_number\": <number>, \"saved\": true, \"action\": \"updated\"}\n4. IF RECORD DOES NOT EXIST (search returns empty or no row_number):\n   - Use \"Append row in sheet in Google Sheets\" tool to create new row with name, linkedin, and description\n   - Immediately after appending, use \"Get row count after append\" tool to get the total number of rows\n   - The row_number of the newly appended row = total row count (because the new row is the last row)\n   - Return JSON: {\"name\": \"exact name\", \"linkedin\": \"url\", \"description\": \"text\", \"row_number\": <total row count>, \"saved\": true, \"action\": \"created\"}\n\nCRITICAL: \n- After appending a new row, ALWAYS call \"Get row count after append\" to determine the correct row_number\n- The row_number must be accurate because the Scoring Agent uses it to update the score and reasoning columns\n- Row 1 is the header row, so data rows start at row 2"
        }
      },
